      • cross

        public static Vector3 cross(Vector3 v1,
                            Vector3 v2)
        Calculates and returns the cross product of the two vectors. Following the formula: cx = aybz − azby cy = azbx − axbz cz = axby − aybx
        Parameters:
        v1 - The first vector.
        v2 - The second vector.
        Returns:
        The resulting Vector3 of the cross product.
